Third-party attribution
-----------------------

The slide-clone relationship-rewriting semantics in utils/clone_utils.py
are re-implemented from (not copied out of) the following MIT-licensed
sources:

* pptx-automizer (https://github.com/singerla/pptx-automizer)
  Copyright (c) singerla (github.com/singerla) and contributors.
  MIT License.
  Ported semantics: per-relationship-type handlers (image / media /
  hyperlink) and the "assertRelatedContent" pattern -- a final safety
  sweep that copies any remaining unhandled relationship target so no
  broken relationship survives the clone.

* python-pptx, pull request #1141
  (https://github.com/scanny/python-pptx/pull/1141)
  python-pptx Copyright (c) 2013 Steve Canny and contributors.
  MIT License.
  Ported semantics: SlidePart clone with relationships re-created in
  ascending rId order.

The effective-style resolver (utils/resolve_core.py,
utils/resolve_theme.py, utils/resolve_colors.py,
utils/resolve_text_props.py, utils/resolve_shape_props.py,
utils/resolve_utils.py) re-implements (does not copy) logic and
architecture from:

* ShapeCrawler (https://github.com/ShapeCrawler/ShapeCrawler)
  Copyright (c) ShapeCrawler contributors.
  MIT License.
  Ported semantics: placeholder matching by type+idx with type-only
  fallback (SCPShapeTree); the placeholder text-inheritance walk across
  layout/master placeholder list styles and master txStyles
  (ReferencedFont, PortionFontSize); the normAutofit fontScale rule --
  scaling applies only to run-level rPr sizes (PortionFontSize);
  lvl1-9pPr per-indent-level extraction (IndentFonts); schemeClr ->
  clrMap -> clrScheme color resolution (PresentationColor, HexParser);
  +mj-lt/+mn-lt theme font token mapping (TextPortionFont); reading the
  shape p:style fontRef color for text in styled shapes (ShapeColor,
  FontColor).

* Apache POI (https://github.com/apache/poi)
  Copyright the Apache Software Foundation.
  Apache License 2.0.
  Ported architecture: the single generic property-fetcher cascade
  walker parameterized by per-property extractor callables
  (XSLF CharacterPropertyFetcher / ParagraphPropertyFetcher); the
  tint/shade-in-sRGB + luminance/saturation-in-HSL color transform
  split (XSLFColor); the shape style-matrix resolution -- lnRef/fillRef
  indexing into the theme fmtScheme with phClr substitution and the
  fillRef >=1000 background-fill offset, and consulting the fontRef
  layer after the placeholder chain but before presentation/theme
  defaults (XSLFSimpleShape, XSLFTextRun).

The paragraph-spacing and bullet cascades (spcBef/spcAft/lnSpc,
buChar/buAutoNum/buNone with independently-inheriting buFont/buSzPct/
buClr) have no reference implementation in either project and are
original to this repository, built on the same walker and verified
against PowerPoint COM-reported effective values.

No source code was copied from these projects; the implementation in this
repository is original Python written against the python-pptx API.
